text: The Maurine is a tributary of the Stepenitz in the extreme northwest corner of Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Germany. ==Course of the river== The Maurine originates between Carlow and Groß Rünz in the southwest of the district Nordwestmecklenburg in a forest and meadow area 45 m above mean sea level. The difference in height from the source to the delta is approximately 45 m. ==External links== * Stepenitz and Maurine Lowlands Category:Rivers of Mecklenburg-Vorpommern Category:Rivers of Germany
